snippet: Tiger Woods shot a nine-under-par 61 in the second round of the Bridgestone Invitational, missing two short birdie putts down the stretch.
abstract: Tiger Woods shoots a 61 to maintain lead after second round of Bridgestone Invitational; pursuit of golf’s magic score of 59 has been a wild ride in 2013, with two minor tour players reaching it, 16-year-old amateur carding one and Phil Mickelson leaving a putt hanging on the lip to barely miss the milestone.
lead_paragraph: Tiger Woods shot a nine-under-par 61 in the second round of the Bridgestone Invitational, missing two short birdie putts down the stretch.

headline.main: Pursuing Elusive 59, Woods Falls a Bit Short
headline.print_headline: In Chase for Elusive 59, Woods Falls Short but Settles for Lead
